  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      -  Describe blood pressure changes on patients with OSA treated with lateral pharyngoplasty

        -  Compare the mean of systolic and diastolic blood pressure in 24 hours, average systolic
           and diastolic pressure during daytime and night and changes in the nocturnal decrease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The variables are:

      Ambulatory blood pressure data Snoring scale BMI neck circumference abdominal circumference
      medications and life style changes
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
